data.toolTip:
The VISA® debit card is free with any KeyPoint checking account, and includes FREE Passport Rewards! You can use the card to withdraw cash, deposit money and make purchases wherever Visa® cards are accepted.

You’ll get access to more than 30,000 fee-free ATMs nationwide through the CO-OP network. When you sign up for a KeyPoint Unlimited Checking account you can use any ATM in the world and we will rebate your ATM fees.

Enjoy Additional Visa® Debit Card Features

Mobile Wallets: Add your card to Apple Pay™, Android Pay or Samsung Pay for added protection.
Passport Rewards: Get discounts for dining, shopping, retail and travel. Register your KeyPoint Visa® Debit Card today and start saving instantly with participating merchants, retailers and special offers.
New EMV Chip Technology: Enjoy advanced security with EMV chip technology.
Visa Checkout and Verified by Visa® : Register for the programs that help prevent unauthorized use of your card for online purchases.
Protection from fraud with Visa’s Zero Liability Policy (you won't be held responsible for fraudulent charges made with your card or account information)
Monitor your checking account 24/7 with Debit Card Alerts that notify you by email and text when certain types of transactions occur.
Debit Card Fraud Protection: We monitor your card activity and take action any time we see suspicious activity.
Travel Watch: Prevent unwanted fraud blocks when traveling internationally by completing a Travel Notification Form before you leave the country.

Checks make it easy to pay anybody when an electronic transfer won’t do. Checks provide a built-in paper trail, documenting how much money you paid.

Your account will be charged for your check order. For more information, contact (888) 255-3637 or visit us in person.

Convenient and Safe! It’s easy to manage your money and stay on top of your finances 24/7 –– with KeyPoint’s Online and Mobile Banking.

Utilizing the latest state-of-the-art technology, our Online and Mobile Banking platforms give you unlimited free access to your KeyPoint accounts –– so it’s easy to:

View account balances, transactions and cleared check images

Pay bills
Transfer funds
Schedule alerts
Deposit checks
Get your FICO® score

And after you enroll in Online Banking, all you have to do is download our Mobile Banking app –– and you can start banking with your smartphone or tablet.

Enhanced security


You have the security of knowing your accounts and personal information are protected with the latest technology available, including:

Secure Socket Layers (SSL)
Multi-Factor-Authentication
Out-of-Band Authentication

And if you do experience fraud, you can limit your losses –– if you call the Contact Center and report it immediately.

Overdraft protection allows funds to be transferred from a previously designated KeyPoint deposit account or credit line on which you are an owner or borrower to pay an overdraft item. For a line of credit to be available for overdraft protection, you must complete an application, receive credit approval, and designate the line as an overdraft protection source.</br></br>Overdraft protection will always be available, so long as your designated overdraft protection source accounts have sufficient available funds or credit. If you access a line of credit, interest will accrue on the amount advanced. Overdraft protection will help protect your checking account from having a negative balance.

Telephone Banking is available 24 hours a day.  Use your phone to get balances, make transfers and get details on transactions.</br></br>Telephone Banking numbers:</br></br>Local (408) 245-0104</br>Toll Free (888) 844-3279

KeyPoint offers Courtesy Pay Privilege as an additional service that spares you the embarrassment or extra fees of having a check returned unpaid due to insufficient funds. At our discretion, we may pay items that draw your checking balance negative. The fee for each Courtesy Pay Privilege payment is $29.00.

Save a tree and simplify your life with free eStatements!

No more paper cuts, waiting for the mail, or managing paper files. Sign up for eStatements and you can access your KeyPoint account statements in Online Banking. You’ll receive your statements faster, and they’ll be securely stored. You’ll be notified by email as soon as your eStatement is available.

Simply click on the eStatements link in Online Banking. It’s that simple!
